  "common": {
    "name": {
      "zh": "HK UCP 4.6x30 手枪",
      "en": "HK UCP 4.6x30 pistol"
    },
    "shortName": {
      "zh": "UCP",
      "en": "UCP"
    },
    "description": {
      "zh": "UCP（全称Universal Combat Pistol，亦称P46）是一款由H&K 公司受德国联邦国防军委托研发的原型双动半自动手枪。该枪采用滚柱延迟后坐式原理运作，其外观设计明显借鉴了P2000手枪，包括双侧操控部件、可更换式握把背板以及符合MIL-STD-1913标准的皮卡汀尼导轨。作为MP7个人防卫武器的配套副武器，UCP同样使用4.6×30毫米瓶颈型弹药。在此背景下，UCP可视作FN赫斯塔尔公司Five-seveN手枪的竞品，与MP7和P90的竞争关系如出一辙。",
      "en": "The UCP (short for Universal Combat Pistol, also known as the P46) is a prototype double-action, semi-automatic pistol that was developed by Heckler & Koch under commission for the Bundeswehr. The UCP operates by roller-delayed blowback. The external design of the weapon appears to have been borrowed from the P2000, including ambidextrous controls, interchangeable backstraps, and a MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail for accessories. It was designed to be the companion sidearm to the MP7 PDW, using the same 4.6×30mm bottlenecked cartridge. In this sense, the UCP was a competitor to FN Herstal's Five-seveN in the same context that the MP7 rivals the P90."
    },
